      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHES A DELANEY (1) was an impressive winner of the Listed Pink Bonnet at Menangle last start, leading from a couple of spots wider before getting home by close to 9 metres. Has been kept up to the mark with a trial win since and can take full advantage of the ace draw. KAHULA (10) is a daughter of champion sire Bettors Delight from a Group 1 winner and is on debut for the powerhouse Emma Stewart stable. Draws on the back row but was close-up in her latest trial at Melton and is sure to be well educated. TEERDEE (4) has come from tougher draws to place in her three starts to date. Copped a check and broke when runner-up last time at Melton. Go well. PEWRIFY (7) made a strong debut as a hot favourite in SA, leading from this barrier to score by close to 4 metres at Globe Derby. Interesting to see her make the trek to NSW so include.",
